nnel of gap fluctuations. We extend the analysis to the case where the\npairing component of the interaction has additional factor $1/N$ and show that\nthere exists a critical $N_{cr} >1$, above which superconductivity disappears,\nand the ground state becomes a non-Fermi liquid.We show that all solutions\ndevelop simultaneously once $N$ gets smaller than $N_{cr}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Apr 2020 00:26:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Aug 2020 21:24:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-05"}
