significant enhancement in\nalbedo is also seen when cloud particles occur with a locally changing Gaussian\nsize distribution. Non-spherical particles increase the opacity of silicate\nspectral features, which further increases the wavelength at which the clouds\nbecome optically thin. JWST MIRI will be sensitive to signatures of\nmicro-porous and non-spherical cloud particles based on the wavelength at which\nclouds are optically thin.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Apr 2020 13:35:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-22"}
